We get the above error with Bamboo Server 6.2.5. Please advise.

h3. Summary
In Repsitory Stored Specs, when we do a force Git push, whenever a commit is triggered and Bamboo Specs checks for commits to that repository that contain specs changes, the below exception is encountered:

{noformat}
2017-11-08 16:51:54,968 INFO [AtlassianEvent::0-BAM::EVENTS:pool-1-thread-5] [BambooSpecsHandlerForGit] Commit 0f3310a03ca11db03e80823c01fb0e6f4095817c not found in the repository. Assuming force push or repository reconfigured
...
Caused by: com.atlassian.bamboo.repository.RepositoryException: Unable to check ancestry between 0f3310a03ca11db03e80823c01fb0e6f4095817c and 7e191c0039327e485c6fd6e2b8bdf0ae653fd4a3 in /var/atlassian/bamboo/xml-data/build-dir/_git-repositories-cache/88fa8b4b64ec631c78e40d5dcd0f6e5bc78b2296
	at com.atlassian.bamboo.plugins.git.GitCommandProcessor.isAncestor(GitCommandProcessor.java:268)
{noformat}

h3. Steps to Reproduce
# Do a git rebase to change the history of the existing commits in the local repository
# Do a force push to the Bitbucket repository that holds Bamboo specs

h3. Expected Results
Upon a successful push, the {{BranchChangedEventListener}} event is recorded in Bamboo.
Bamboo should intelligently identify Specs changes and a force push has been detected. It should continue building Specs without any error.
{noformat}
2017-11-15 15:10:19,537 INFO [http-nio-8085-exec-15] [AccessLogFilter] 192.168.1.10 POST http://192.168.1.10:8085/rest/remote-event-consumer/latest/events/stash-branch-changed-remote-event 57031kb
2017-11-15 15:10:19,555 INFO [AtlassianEvent::0-BAM::EVENTS:pool-1-thread-11] [BranchChangedEventListener] Received Bitbucket Server ref changed event [WHAT/iamsterdam, master]
2017-11-15 15:10:20,146 INFO [AtlassianEvent::0-BAM::EVENTS:pool-1-thread-11] [BranchChangedEventListener] Detected a possible Bamboo spec change in repository. Running update.
{noformat}

h3. Actual Results
The below exception is thrown in the {{catalina.out}} file:
{noformat}
2017-11-08 16:51:54,968 INFO [AtlassianEvent::0-BAM::EVENTS:pool-1-thread-5] [BambooSpecsHandlerForGit] Commit 0f3310a03ca11db03e80823c01fb0e6f4095817c not found in the repository. Assuming force push or repository reconfigured
...
Caused by: com.atlassian.bamboo.repository.RepositoryException: Unable to check ancestry between 0f3310a03ca11db03e80823c01fb0e6f4095817c and 7e191c0039327e485c6fd6e2b8bdf0ae653fd4a3 in /var/atlassian/bamboo/xml-data/build-dir/_git-repositories-cache/88fa8b4b64ec631c78e40d5dcd0f6e5bc78b2296
	at com.atlassian.bamboo.plugins.git.GitCommandProcessor.isAncestor(GitCommandProcessor.java:268)
{noformat}
 
h3.Workaround
Find the latest entry and copy the vcs_specs_state_id value from it.
{noformat}
select * from vcs_specs_state where vcs_location_id=884737;
{noformat}
Now, run the below query by replacing 
* vcs_specs_state_id with the value we just copied
* Latest SHA commitID with IncomingCommitID value. Eg. 7e191c0039327e485c6fd6e2b8bdf0ae653fd4a3

{noformat}
update vcs_specs_state
set revision='<IncomingCommitID>'
where vcs_specs_state_id={{vcs_specs_state_id}};
{noformat}

h3. Summary
[Bamboo REST API documentation|https://docs.atlassian.com/atlassian-bamboo/REST/6.2.3] are missing information about body request, so developers/users attempting on running them can struggle on providing permissions.

h3. Steps to Reproduce

{color:blue}/permissions/environment/\{id}/groups/\{name : (.+)?}{color}
*resource-wide template parameters*
||parameter||value||description||
|name|string|affected group|
|id|string|deployment environment entity key|

Attempt on running any of the following endpoint:
{noformat}
curl -k -u ADMIN_USER:PASSWORD \
     -H "Content-type: application/json" \
     -H "Accept: application/json" \
     -X DELETE http://myhost.com:8085/bamboo/rest/api/latest/permissions/environment/{id}/groups/{name : (.+)?}
{noformat}

h4. Project Plan
{noformat}
http://myhost.com:8085/bamboo/rest/api/latest/permissions/projectplan/{key}/users/{name : (.+)?} [PUT, DELETE]
http://myhost.com:8085/bamboo/rest/api/latest/permissions/projectplan/{key}/groups/{name : (.+)?} [PUT, DELETE]
http://myhost.com:8085/bamboo/rest/api/latest/permissions/projectplan/{key}/roles/{name : (.+)?} [PUT, DELETE]
{noformat}

h4. Plan
{noformat}
http://myhost.com:8085/bamboo/rest/api/latest/permissions/plan/{key}/users/{name : (.+)?} [PUT, DELETE]
http://myhost.com:8085/bamboo/rest/api/latest/permissions/plan/{key}/groups/{name : (.+)?} [PUT, DELETE]
http://myhost.com:8085/bamboo/rest/api/latest/permissions/plan/{key}/roles/{name : (.+)?} [PUT, DELETE]
{noformat}

h4. Repository
{noformat}
http://myhost.com:8085/bamboo/rest/api/latest/permissions/repository/{id}/users/{name : (.+)?} [PUT, DELETE]
http://myhost.com:8085/bamboo/rest/api/latest/permissions/repository/{id}/groups/{name : (.+)?} [PUT, DELETE]
http://myhost.com:8085/bamboo/rest/api/latest/permissions/repository/{id}/roles/{name : (.+)?} [PUT, DELETE]
{noformat}

h4. Project
{noformat}
http://myhost.com:8085/bamboo/rest/api/latest/permissions/global/users/{name : (.+)?} [PUT, DELETE]
http://myhost.com:8085/bamboo/rest/api/latest/permissions/global/groups/{name : (.+)?} [PUT, DELETE]
http://myhost.com:8085/bamboo/rest/api/latest/permissions/global/roles/{name : (.+)?} [PUT, DELETE]
{noformat}

h4. Environment
{noformat}
http://myhost.com:8085/bamboo/rest/api/latest/permissions/environment/{id}/users/{name : (.+)?} [PUT, DELETE]
http://myhost.com:8085/bamboo/rest/api/latest/permissions/environment/{id}/groups/{name : (.+)?} [PUT, DELETE]
http://myhost.com:8085/bamboo/rest/api/latest/permissions/environment/{id}/roles/{name : (.+)?} [PUT, DELETE]
{noformat}

h4. Deployment
{noformat}
http://myhost.com:8085/bamboo/rest/api/latest/permissions/deployment/{id}/users/{name : (.+)?} [PUT, DELETE]
http://myhost.com:8085/bamboo/rest/api/latest/permissions/deployment/{id}/groups/{name : (.+)?} [PUT, DELETE]
http://myhost.com:8085/bamboo/rest/api/latest/permissions/deployment/{id}/roles/{name : (.+)?} [PUT, DELETE]
{noformat}

h3. Expected Results
Error being thrown because no permission for deletion was passed

h3. Actual Results
No error gets thrown or a warning message stating no permission was passed

h3. Notes
Permission {color:blue}@RequestBody final List<String> permissionsToRemove{color} should be passed on as list, e.g:
{noformat}
["READ","BUILD","WRITE"]
{noformat}
As a result, the REST API call in example given should be:
{noformat}
curl -k -u ADMIN_USER:PASSWORD \
     -H "Content-type: application/json" \
     -H "Accept: application/json" \
     -d '["READ","BUILD","WRITE"]'
     -X DELETE http://myhost.com:8085/bamboo/rest/api/latest/permissions/environment/{id}/groups/{name : (.+)?}
{noformat}

Currently, Bamboo allows using Global variables as part of a Git repository address, this possibility could be improved to allow using plan variables such ${bamboo.planKey} and ${bamboo.shortPlanName}.

h3. Current behavior:
 
Ropository address set to:

{code:java}
http://bitbucket:7990/scm/proj/${bamboo.shortPlanName}.git
{code}

The plan fails with an error similar to this:

{noformat}
 Errors getting changes for PROJ-PLAN-15 
(com.atlassian.bamboo.plugins.git.GitCommandException : command /usr/bin/git ls-remote http://********:********@bitbucket:7990/scm/proj/${bamboo.shortPlanName}.git failed with code 128. Working directory was [.]., stderr: fatal: unable to access 'http://********:********@bitbucket:7990/scm/proj/${bamboo.shortPlanName}.git/': The requested URL returned error: 400)
{noformat}

When exporting Bamboo specs, one will find that the variables are all encrypted with the same cipher, which can be considered insecure.

{code}
new Variable("PASSWORD",
"BAMSCRT@0@0@mE/<some string>=="))
{code}

Compare the encrypted value for PASSWORD with the same in the spec for a different build plan:
{code}
new Variable("PASSWORD",
"BAMSCRT@0@0@mE/<some string>=="))
{code}
